Nippon Life Asks Olympus to Take ‘Prompt’ Action on Concerns

-- B y   M a r i k o   Y a s u
-- 
2011-10-20T06:15:34Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-20/nippon-life-asks-olympus-to-take-prompt-action-on-concerns.html
Nippon Life Insurance Co., the
biggest shareholder of  Olympus Corp. (7733) , asked the Japanese camera
maker to take “prompt” action to address investor concern and
distrust regarding the company’s corporate governance, according
to an e-mail from Akira Tsuzuki, a Tokyo-based spokesman for
Nippon Life.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Mariko Yasu in Tokyo at 
